  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various methods, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Establishing mandatory reporting thresholds\n\n2. Investigation Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing money trails\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Using advanced digital forensic tools\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated enforcement efforts\n\n4. Criminal Prosecution\n- Pursuing criminal charges against perpetrators\n- Seizing illicit assets\n- Imposing significant financial penalties\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight\n- Monitoring financial institutions\n- Conducting compliance audits\n- Implementing strict reporting requirements\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
